"a.不定时发生的 【英】 adj.不定时发生的(oc curring occasionally) 【考】 反义词：chronic(长 期的) 【例】 sound of sporadic gunfire adj. 不定时发生的 【记】spor = sper发散, 散发, adic: 发散的－不定期的 【反】chronic(adj 长期持续的); regular(adj 规则的; 定期的); frequent(adj 时常发生的) 【记】spore 孢子是零星存在的，象蒲公英的种子飘来飘去的，零零星星的 sporadic (adj.)  1680s, from Medieval Latin sporadicus ""scattered,"" from Greek sporadikos ""scattered,"" from sporas (genitive sporados) ""scattered, dispersed,"" from spora ""a sowing"" (see spore). Originally a medical term, ""occurring in scattered instances;"" the meaning ""happening at intervals"" is first recorded 1847. Related: Sporadical (1650s); sporadically."
